 tcp 10.233.46.196:7070: i/o timeout' and 'timed out waiting for server handshake' - 164 occurrences with 100% error rate\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"checkoutservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\", \n      \"evidence\": \"CheckoutService PlaceOrder calls experiencing extreme latency: normal 145-156ms vs anomaly 23.6-24.8 seconds (150-175x increase)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"frontend\",\n      \"reason\": \"error_ratio\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Frontend receiving HTTP 500 errors due to CheckoutService failures - 238 occurrences across all frontend instances\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Key Findings:\n\n**Root Cause**: **CartService Unavailability**\n- CartService (IP: 10.233.46.196:7070) is completely unreachable during the fault period\n- All calls to CartService timeout with connection errors\n- This affects CheckoutService's ability to retrieve user carts during checkout\n\n**Impact Propagation**:\n1. **CartService** → Unavailable (root cause)\n2. **CheckoutService** → Extreme latency (23-25 seconds vs normal 150ms) due to CartService timeouts\n3. **Frontend** → HTTP 500 errors cascading from CheckoutService failures\n\n**Critical Evidence**:\n- CartService GetCart operations show 100% failure rate with timeout errors\n- CheckoutService PlaceOrder latency increased by 150-175x\n- Frontend receives cascading errors from downstream service failures\n\nThe fault chain is clear: CartService failure → CheckoutService timeout → Frontend errors. CartService is the definitive root cause based on the error patterns and dependency topology.", "metric_analysis_findings": "Based on my analysis of the metric data during the fault period, I've identified several significant anomalies. Here's my comprehensive assessment:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\"error_ratio\", \"server_error_ratio\", \"client_error_ratio\", \"rrt\", \"rrt_max\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"checkoutservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"Severe latency degradation with rrt increasing from ~7,000ms to over 4,000,000ms and rrt_max exceeding 20,000,000ms across both instances\",\n      \"evidence\": \"checkoutservice-1: rrt increased from 7,488ms to 3,440,797ms (99.3% increase), checkoutservice-2: rrt increased from 6,936ms to 4,001,602ms (99.3% increase)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"frontend\",\n      \"reason\": \"Significant error ratio increase and latency spikes across all three instances, with error_ratio reaching 30-32% and rrt_max exceeding 20,000,000ms\",\n      \"evidence\": \"frontend-0: error_ratio increased from 0% to 32%, rrt_max increased from 260,959ms to 20,008,908ms; frontend-1: error_ratio 0% to 29%, rrt_max 280,746ms to 27,461,909ms\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"cartservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"High client error ratio reaching 47.65% and significant rrt_max degradation in cartservice-1 instance\",\n      \"evidence\": \"cartservice-1: client_error_ratio p99 increased to 47.65%, rrt_max increased from 5,209ms to 22,501,013ms (99.3% increase)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"shippingservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"Extremely high client error ratio reaching 60% p99 values across multiple instances\",\n      \"evidence\": \"shippingservice-1 and shippingservice-2 both showing client_error_ratio p99 values of 60% during fault period\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Key Findings:\n\n1. **Primary Performance Degradation**: The checkoutservice shows the most severe latency issues with response times increasing by over 99% across both instances.\n\n2. **Cascading Error Impact**: The frontend service experiences high error rates (30-32%) likely due to downstream service failures, particularly from checkoutservice.\n\n3. **Distributed Error Pattern**: Multiple services (cartservice, shippingservice) show elevated error ratios, suggesting a systemic issue affecting the entire application stack.\n\n4. **Latency Domino Effect**: The rrt_max metric shows catastrophic degradation across multiple services, indicating a cascading failure pattern where slow responses from one service impact others.\n\nThe fault appears to be a distributed system performance degradation starting with checkoutservice and propagating through the service mesh to frontend and other dependent services."}
